{
  "texts": [
    "This allows us to compare directly to the non-conditional MPGAN model.",
    "6 For these comparisons we calculate the relative transverse momentum (p rel T) of each constituent using the full p T of the jet.We look at the relative transverse momentum p rel T and relative invariant mass m rel jet of the reconstructed jet.",
    "These observables are calculated from the vector sum of the 30 (leading in p T) jet constituents using p rel T in place of p T per constituent.",
    "These are shown in Figs.",
    "3 and 4 for gluon jets and top jets, respectively."
  ]
}